# Part 2

## Describe an occasion when you had a special cake.

One special cake that I remember very clearly was the cake I received on my twentieth birthday last year. It happened during my first semester at university, when I was really busy with coursework and preparing for several exams. To be honest, I almost forgot that my birthday was coming because I had been spending most of my time in the library.

That evening, a few of my close friends invited me to a small café near our campus. At first, I thought we were just going there to have dinner together, but when the lights suddenly dimmed, they brought out a beautifully decorated cake and started singing “Happy Birthday”. I was genuinely surprised because I hadn’t expected anyone to organize something like that for me.

The cake itself was quite special. It wasn’t an ordinary cream cake from a supermarket. One of my friends actually designed it specifically for me. Since I’m really interested in artificial intelligence and programming, the cake was decorated with elements related to technology, like tiny chocolate keyboards, computer chips, and even the NVIDIA logo made from icing. I thought it was incredibly creative and thoughtful.

What made the cake truly unforgettable wasn’t just its appearance or taste, although it was delicious. It was special because it reminded me that even during stressful periods, I still had people around me who cared about me. As a university student, there are times when I feel overwhelmed by academic pressure, so that moment gave me a strong sense of warmth and support. Even now, whenever I look back on that day, I still feel grateful and happy.

---

### 中文翻译：

我印象特别深刻的一次“特别的蛋糕”是在去年我20岁生日的时候。那时正好是我大学第一学期，我忙着完成课程作业和准备考试。老实说，因为大部分时间都泡在图书馆，我差点忘了自己的生日。

那天晚上，我几个关系很好的朋友邀请我去学校附近的一家小咖啡馆。一开始我以为只是普通聚餐，但当灯光突然暗下来时，他们推着一个漂亮的蛋糕出来，还一起唱生日歌。我当时真的特别惊喜，因为完全没想到有人会为我准备这些。

那个蛋糕本身也非常特别。它不是普通的奶油蛋糕，而是朋友专门根据我的兴趣设计的。因为我对人工智能和编程特别感兴趣，蛋糕上有很多科技元素，比如巧克力键盘、电脑芯片，甚至还有用糖霜做的 NVIDIA 标志。我觉得既有创意又很用心。

不过，这个蛋糕真正特别的地方并不只是外观或者味道，虽然它确实很好吃。更重要的是，它让我意识到，即使在压力很大的阶段，身边依然有人关心我。作为大学生，我有时会因为学业压力感到疲惫，而那一刻给了我很强的温暖和支持感。直到现在，每次回忆起那天，我都会觉得特别感激和开心。

